    intro: "Tupran (also spelled Toopran) is a mandal headquarters and municipality in Medak district, designated as an urban node in the HMDA Master Plan 2031. The mandal comprises multiple villages and has a population of 53,332 across 10,556 households (Census 2011). This page displays the Master Plan as an interactive overlay on satellite imagery, allowing you to search a survey number or landmark and toggle the zoning layer to identify land-use designations and reserved areas.",
    paragraphs: ["Tupran is strategically located with connectivity to major transportation routes. As a designated urban node in the HMDA regional plan, Tupran is positioned for growth as a secondary urban center within the Hyderabad metropolitan region, with ongoing HMDA-approved residential and commercial layouts.","Use the map tool to enter your survey number or local landmark, then toggle the Master Plan overlay on or off to verify the zoned land use and any reserved areas before making planning or investment decisions. The plan extends to 2031 and indicates public facility reservations, green space and transport alignment."],
