    intro: "Wargal is the mandal headquarters of Wargal mandal in Siddipet district (administratively reorganized from Medak district in 2016). The mandal comprises 22 villages and falls within HMDA Master Plan 2031 coverage. This page overlays the Master Plan as an interactive tool on satellite imagery, enabling you to search a survey number or local landmark and toggle the zoning view to confirm land-use designation and development reservations.",
    paragraphs: ["Wargal was reorganized from Medak district to Siddipet district following the 2016 Telangana district reorganization. Despite the administrative change, Wargal remains integrated into the HMDA Master Plan 2031 framework covering the expanded Hyderabad metropolitan region.","Use the map to search your survey number or nearby landmark, then toggle the Master Plan overlay to confirm the zoned land use and any reserved areas for public infrastructure. The plan extends to 2031 and indicates reservations for transportation, green space and community facilities."],
