    intro: "Bhor is the administrative headquarters of Bhor taluka in Pune district and is governed by the Bhor Municipal Council. Located approximately 50 km south of Pune city, Bhor taluka encompasses 53 villages under PMRDA jurisdiction and is primarily agricultural with a blend of rural and semi-urban zones. This page displays the Development Plan overlay on satellite imagery to help you identify land-use classifications, reservations, and plot boundaries.",
    paragraphs: ["Bhor taluka is situated in the Haveli subdivision of Pune district, one of the administrative subdivisions in the PMRDA region. The taluka is approximately 50.5 km south of the PMRDA district headquarters and features significant agricultural pursuits alongside emerging infrastructure development. PMRDA oversees taluka road projects and sewerage infrastructure planning across Bhor's 53 villages, supporting orderly expansion alongside agricultural preservation.","Search for survey numbers, village names, or landmarks within Bhor taluka on this Development Plan map. Toggle the overlay to compare designated zones (agricultural, residential, reserved areas) with satellite imagery. This is particularly useful for understanding land-use restrictions, road reservations, and development potential before planning agricultural transitions or residential projects in taluka areas."],
