    intro: "Pashan is a research and institutional hub in Haveli taluka, Pune, home to ARDE, DRDO, IISER, National Chemical Laboratory and other government research establishments. It borders Pashan Lake, a manmade reservoir on the Ramnadi river that attracts migratory birds. This page opens the Development Plan as an interactive overlay on satellite imagery, allowing you to identify land-use zones, reservations and road boundaries for any surveyed plot in Pashan.",
    paragraphs: ["Pashan lies approximately 12 km south of Pune city center, within Haveli taluka. The area spans 1,048 hectares (revenue village) and is part of the Kothrud Vidhan Sabha constituency. The geography features significant hill area—Pashan has the maximum hill coverage (5,111.89 hectares) within Pune Municipal Corporation limits.","To use this map: search for a specific survey number, landmark, or institution by name. Toggle the Development Plan overlay on and off to view the designated zone, road reservations and land-use category. This helps confirm zoning before relying on it for property transactions or development inquiries."],
