    intro: "Kothrud is an upmarket residential suburb in west-central Pune, historically known as Kothrud Baug during the Maratha era. It hosts the Automotive Research Association of India, engineering colleges, and has its own state assembly (Vidhan Sabha) constituency. This page opens the Development Plan as an interactive overlay showing land-use zones, reservations and roads for any plot, enabling you to verify zoning before property transactions.",
    paragraphs: ["Kothrud lies in west-central Pune and is governed by Pune Municipal Corporation. It underwent major residential redevelopment from the early 2000s onward, with older structures being replaced by taller buildings. It benefits from proximity to Vetal Tekdi hills and modern metro connectivity via the Pune Metro Aqua Line, which serves the area.","To use this map: search by survey number, locality name or landmark. Toggle the Development Plan overlay to view the designated land-use zone, road widening reservations and administrative boundaries. This confirms zoning for property analysis or development planning."],
