    keywords: ["dhankwadi development plan","dhankwadi zone map","dhankwadi katraj lake","dhankwadi zoo location","dhankwadi pict","dhankwadi land use","dhankwadi survey number"],
    intro: "Dhankwadi is a locality approximately 6.5 km south of Pune city, incorporated into Pune Municipal Corporation in 1997. It is known for Katraj Lake (featuring an island with a statue of Shivaji Maharaj), the Rajiv Gandhi Zoological Park, and educational institutions including PICT (Pune Institute of Computer Technology) and Bharati Vidyapeeth Deemed University. The area has become a pilgrimage centre due to Sant Sadguru Shri Shankar Maharaj. This page opens the Development Plan as an interactive map overlay showing zones, reservations and road boundaries for property verification.",
    paragraphs: ["Dhankwadi was originally a small village in Purandar Taluka and was merged into Pune Municipal Corporation on September 11, 1997, as part of a major municipal expansion that incorporated 23 villages into the city. The locality is well-connected via the Mumbai-Pune Bypass Road and local bus stops.","To use this map: search for a survey number, road or landmark within Dhankwadi. Toggle the Development Plan layer to view the designated land-use zone (residential, recreational, educational, etc.), road reservations and administrative boundaries. This assists in confirming plot classification and road access before transactions or approvals."],
