    keywords: ["indapur development plan","indapur taluka land use zones","indapur pune map","indapur municipal council","indapur baramati subdivision","development plan pune district"],
    intro: "Indapur is a town and municipal council serving as the administrative headquarters of Indapur taluka in Baramati subdivision, Pune district. Located approximately 154 km east of Pune city, it holds historical significance as the ancestral seat of Malojiraje Bhosale, grandfather of Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj. This page displays the Development Plan as an interactive overlay on satellite imagery, enabling you to identify the designated zone, reservations, and road lines for any survey number or location within the taluka.",
    paragraphs: ["Indapur taluka lies in Baramati subdivision about 154 km east of Pune district headquarters. The taluka supports a population of approximately 383,183 (2011 census) across 102 villages, with the town of Indapur (25,515 residents) serving as its administrative centre. Malojiraje, a Maratha sardar and ancestor of Shivaji Maharaj, held Indapur as a key jagir; his samadhi is located in the town.","To use the Development Plan map: search your survey number or landmark in Indapur taluka, then toggle the overlay to reveal the designated land-use zone (agricultural, residential, commercial, industrial, or special use). Check for road widening lines or utility corridors that may affect your property before finalizing purchases or planning developments."],
