    description: "Development Plan map overlay for Daund taluka, Pune district Maharashtra. View zones and land-use designations on satellite imagery with road and rail corridor reservations.",
    keywords: ["daund development plan","daund taluka land use map","daund pune","daund railway junction","daund municipal council","daund taluka zones"],
    intro: "Daund is a municipal council and taluka headquarters in Pune district, located approximately 83.4 km east of the district capital. It serves as a major railway junction on the Mumbai-Chennai route and plays a pivotal role as a freight redistribution hub for multiple railway lines. This page opens the Development Plan as an interactive map overlay on satellite imagery, allowing you to view designated zones, reservations, and infrastructure corridors for any plot or location within Daund taluka.",
    paragraphs: ["Daund taluka is situated on the Bhima River about 83.4 km east of Pune district headquarters. The taluka comprises 102 villages and supports a population of approximately 380,496 (2011 census). The town itself has a municipal council and recorded 49,450 residents in the 2011 census. Daund Junction railway station is a major transport node connecting the Pune-Solapur, Manmad-Daund, and Baramati-Daund rail lines, handling significant freight and passenger traffic.","To use the Development Plan map: locate your survey number, address, or landmark on Daund taluka, then toggle the overlay to see the zoning (residential, commercial, agricultural, industrial, or special use). The map also shows railway corridor reservations and road widening lines—critical for understanding constraints on future construction or property development in this rail-centric region."],
