    description: "Development Plan map for Jath taluka (Sangli district, Maharashtra) showing zone designations, road lines and amenities on satellite overlay. Search survey plots to verify land-use classification.",
    keywords: ["jath development plan","jath taluka zone map","jath sangli planning","jath land use zones","jath survey map online"],
    intro: "Jath is the taluka headquarters of Jath taluka in the Miraj subdivision of Sangli district, Maharashtra. A former princely state and Maratha capital, Jath now serves as the administrative centre for a taluka encompassing 125 villages and a population exceeding 328,000. The renowned Yallamma temple nearby hosts one of the largest annual cattle fairs in southern Maharashtra. This page overlays the Development Plan on satellite imagery to let you pinpoint zones, road reservations and planned facilities for any survey plot.",
    paragraphs: ["Jath taluka spans 2,240 km² (147 people per km²) and lies approximately 58 km east of Sangli district headquarters, toward the Karnataka border. The taluka borders Karnataka to the south and east, with Kannada spoken by 33% of residents alongside Marathi. Agriculture is the primary occupation, with the Yallamma temple cattle fair (held on Chaitra Paurnima) drawing thousands of livestock traders annually.","To locate your plot: search its survey number or a nearby landmark, then toggle the Development Plan layer to see the designated zone (rural, urban, industrial, or agricultural), road widths and future public facilities. Use this to understand permitted uses before acquisition or construction."],
