    description: "Development Plan overlay for Ashta municipal council (Walwa taluka, Sangli district, Maharashtra). Interactive map shows zones and land-use designations on satellite imagery.",
    keywords: ["ashta development plan","ashta municipal council zone","ashta walwa sangli map","ashta land use planning","ashta survey number map"],
    intro: "Ashta is a municipal council in Walwa taluka, Sangli district, Maharashtra, with a population of approximately 37,000 and 7,700 households. The town sits on elevated ground above the fertile Krishna river valley and is known for its rich black soil suited to sugarcane, jowar and groundnut cultivation. One of Maharashtra's oldest municipal councils (established 1853), Ashta serves as a local administrative and agricultural centre. This page opens the Development Plan as an interactive overlay on satellite imagery so you can search a survey number and view the designated zone, road lines and public amenities for your plot.",
    paragraphs: ["Ashta lies in Walwa taluka, approximately 28 km west of Sangli district headquarters and about 19 km southeast of Islampur. The taluka is traversed by the Krishna River and sits at the border of fertile black-soil regions. Ashta is administering 19 electoral wards and managing water, sewerage and road services for the municipality.","To use the map: search your plot's survey number or nearest landmark, then toggle the Development Plan overlay to confirm the land-use zone (residential, commercial, industrial, or agricultural reserve), check road-line width reservations, and identify planned civic infrastructure before relying on any plot for purchase or construction."],
