    description: "Explore Tasgaon Development Plan zones and land-use designations on interactive satellite map. View municipal zones, reservations and road lines for any plot in Sangli district, Maharashtra.",
    keywords: ["tasgaon development plan","tasgaon land use zones","tasgaon municipal council","sangli district town planning","tasgaon survey numbers"],
    intro: "Tasgaon is the administrative headquarters of Tasgaon taluka and a municipal council in Sangli district. Known as the \"City of Grapes,\" it is the centre of India's largest grape and raisin production region, with over 9,000 hectares under grape cultivation. This page opens the Development Plan layer covering Tasgaon as an interactive overlay on satellite imagery, letting you read the land-use zone, reservations and road lines for any plot.",
    paragraphs: ["Tasgaon lies approximately 22 km north of Sangli district headquarters. The town's economy revolves around viticulture and raisin production, with over 100 trading centres and 60-65 cold storage warehouses serving the regional export market. The municipal council, established in 1865 as a Class C municipality, administers 19 wards covering the urban area.","To use the Development Plan map: search for a survey number, landmark, or address in Tasgaon. Toggle the Development Plan overlay on and off to confirm the zone designation (residential, agricultural, industrial, or reserved land) before relying on it for property decisions or planning purposes. The map displays current municipal boundaries and notified Development Plan extents."],
