    intro: "Satara is the district headquarters and taluka headquarters of Satara district, Maharashtra, serving as an administrative and cultural center with significant Maratha heritage. The city's name derives from 'Saat Tara' (Seven Stars) referring to the seven surrounding hill forts. This page opens the Development Plan layer covering Satara Municipal Council as an interactive overlay on satellite imagery so you can read the land-use zone, reservations and road lines for any plot.",
